# Law of Demeter

A method may call only on itself, objects it creates, its parameters, and **direct** components — not on objects returned by those calls.

**Train wreck:** `transport.getChannel().getSession().getStatus()` for business logic.

Complements [stomp4j-tell-dont-ask.mdc](stomp4j-tell-dont-ask.mdc).

## Violations vs fixes

```java
// ❌
if (client.getTransport().getListener().isConnected()) { … }

// ✅
if (client.isConnected()) { … }
// or ask the direct collaborator only
if (transport.isConnected()) { … }
```

## Where it applies

| Layer | Rule |
|-------|------|
| Public API | No reaching into `internal` types from outside the module |
| Session / StompClientImpl | Expose `isConnected()`, `getProtocolVersion()` instead of deep graphs |
| Handlers | Receive only what they need (`topic`, `body`, `OutboundChannel`) |

## Allowed

- One direct component: `message.headers().get(Header.DESTINATION)`.
- Protocol layer building frames from `Headers` and `Command`.
- Test code accessing package-visible test helpers.

## Never

- Copy the same getter chain into a second class — extract a method on the owning type.
- Use `internal` types from handler callbacks registered by consumers.
